description:
The Tri-Stat Core System Role-Playing game is an expanded version ofthe Big Eyes Small Mouth RPG, modified and made more generic to encompass other genres, other styles of play.  

It&amp;#039;s a generic system that focuses on effects-based development with a philosophical approach that flaws should hinder the character... and that some flaws (such as, say, laziness, aren&amp;#039;t actually flaws so much as character choices.

Published by the now-defunct Guardians of Order (GOO), Tri-Stat was a strong Canadian offering to the RPG community.  Sadly, mounting debts and (ironically) a stronger Canadian dollar, did it in.

The final edition of GOO&amp;#039;s BESM has recently been picked up by White Wolf publishing under their Arthause Imprint.  However, this version of the Tri_Stat system was made widely available for free download when it came out.   It&amp;#039;s gotten harder and harder to find a download source for it. 
